AUDEN raced in the four path into the far turn, continued well off the inside into the lane, bid from the five path once straightened in the lane and was gaining to the end. FUNSTRUCK saved ground while never far back, came into the lane as a threat and lacked a finishing response. TAP TARGET was squeezed at the start and settled to near the back, bid three wide into the far turn while in the four path, continued as a threat into the lane and flattened out. RAMSEY raced near the inside into the far turn, came off the inside in late turn and never was a factor. WESTERN MOON chased the pace from the two path into the far turn then tired. ANCIENT MAN chased the pace from the four path into the turn and was done in mid-turn.
